      "writtenOn": "2018-10-11T22:13:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I feel like this is a bit messy (ie this + the .C in the template).\n\nI\u0027d actually prefer adding a new fields to the ui/build.go struct.\neg. add the preference there, and then add parent pointers in buildComponent up to build\nand then expose a \"showPerf\" method that returns the preference from buildComponent.\n\nThis principle here is that if we\u0027re going to make a mess somewhere, it\u0027s better to do it in Go code rather than in the templating code.  Templating code is more prone to errors.\n\nMoreover, the ui/build struct exists only as an in-memory object that represents the interfacing between the template and the backend (ie the \"controller\" of a MVC model).  So it\u0027s appropriate to mold that however you wish.",
      "revId": "fd0c8c6038e91e07408a98c3c7b41c1bded37d6a",
